The paper deals with the representation of planar graphs as tangency graphs of circles, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on convex optimization, which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of circle packing, such as the Circle Packing Theorem and its generalization, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions the applications of circle packing in theoretical computer science, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.GR (computational geometry and topology).
